# Ministry Manager - Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Ministry Manager is a mobile-first web application for church ministry scheduling and management. It helps church managers organize volunteers, create schedules, and manage song lyrics for worship services.

## Tech Stack
- **Framework**: Next.js 16 with App Router (React Server Components enabled)
- **Language**: TypeScript (strict mode)
- **UI Components**: shadcn/ui (new-york style)
- **Styling**: Tailwind CSS 4
- **Icons**: Lucide React
- **Database**: Supabase (PostgreSQL) - *to be integrated later*
- **Authentication**: Supabase Auth - *to be integrated later*

## Development Phase
Currently in **Frontend-Only Phase** using mock/dummy data. Backend integration will come later.

## Mobile-First Design Principles
This app prioritizes mobile users. Follow these guidelines:

### Layout
- Design for 375px width first, then scale up
- Use responsive breakpoints: `sm:` (640px), `md:` (768px), `lg:` (1024px)
- Bottom navigation for mobile, sidebar for desktop
- Touch-friendly tap targets (minimum 44x44px)
- Avoid hover-only interactions

### Typography
- Base font size: 16px minimum for body text
- Use relative units (rem) for scalability
- Ensure readable line heights (1.5-1.75 for body)

### Spacing
- Generous padding for touch interfaces
- Use Tailwind's spacing scale consistently
- Safe area insets for mobile browsers

## Code Conventions

### File Structure
```
app/
├── (auth)/           # Auth routes (login, signup)
├── (dashboard)/      # Protected dashboard routes
├── layout.tsx
├── page.tsx
└── globals.css

components/
├── ui/               # shadcn components
├── layout/           # Layout components (nav, sidebar, header)
├── forms/            # Form components
├── schedule/         # Schedule-related components
├── people/           # People management components
├── calendar/         # Calendar components
└── lyrics/           # Song lyrics components

lib/
├── utils.ts          # Utility functions
├── types.ts          # TypeScript type definitions
├── data/             # Mock data for development
│   ├── people.ts
│   ├── ministries.ts
│   ├── schedules.ts
│   └── songs.ts
└── hooks/            # Custom React hooks

```

### Naming Conventions
- Components: PascalCase (e.g., `PersonCard.tsx`)
- Utilities/hooks: camelCase (e.g., `useSchedule.ts`)
- Types/Interfaces: PascalCase with descriptive names (e.g., `MinistryAssignment`)
- Files: kebab-case for routes, PascalCase for components

### Component Guidelines
- Use Server Components by default
- Add `"use client"` only when needed (interactivity, hooks, browser APIs)
- Prefer shadcn/ui components over custom implementations
- Keep components small and focused
- Extract reusable logic into custom hooks

## Data Models

### Core Types
```typescript
// Person - A church member who can be assigned to ministries
interface Person {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  phone?: string;
  email?: string;
  ministries: Ministry[];
  isActive: boolean;
  createdAt: Date;
}

// Ministry - A service role in the church
type Ministry = 
  | "musician"
  | "usher"
  | "multimedia"
  | "singer"
  | "scripture_reader"
  | "prayer_leader"
  | "host";

// Schedule - A service schedule for a specific date
interface Schedule {
  id: string;
  date: Date;
  serviceType: "sunday_morning" | "sunday_evening" | "midweek" | "special";
  assignments: Assignment[];
  notes?: string;
  createdAt: Date;
}

// Assignment - A person assigned to a ministry for a schedule
interface Assignment {
  id: string;
  scheduleId: string;
  personId: string;
  ministry: Ministry;
  confirmed: boolean;
}

// Song - A worship song with lyrics
interface Song {
  id: string;
  title: string;
  artist?: string;
  lyrics: string;
  key?: string;
  tempo?: string;
  tags: string[];
  createdAt: Date;
}
```

